OL,3,CMan first to be jailed following
OL,4,Cwidespread rioting
OL,6,FMs Black said: "This was in the
OL,7,Fcontext of being involved in a
OL,8,Fsituation with a group of people."
OL,10,FThe court heard Nelson, who has no
OL,11,Fprevious convictions, lives with his
OL,12,Fgrandparents and was said to have
OL,13,Facted 'completely out of character'.
OL,15,FDistrict Judge Joanne Hirst asked the
OL,16,Fdefence barrister: "Why did he attend
OL,17,Fwearing a pink balaclava?" Ms Black
OL,18,Freplied: "I'm not sure."
