OL,3,CMan first to be jailed following
OL,4,Cwidespread rioting
OL,6,FThe judge then asked: "He was trying
OL,7,Fto evade identification, should he be
OL,8,Finvolved in violence?"
OL,10,FMs Black said: "He accepts he was
OL,11,Finvolved in this violence. He brought
OL,12,Fa pink balaclava, though he was
OL,13,Fclearly identified by witnesses. He
OL,14,Fwas not thinking properly, he was
OL,15,Fimmature and naive to the gravity of
OL,16,Fthe consequences of the offences he
OL,17,Fcommitted."
OL,19,FNelson, of Victoria Road, Bolton, was
OL,20,Fjailed for two months and ordered to
OL,21,Fpay #4,999 in compensation.
